click to enlarge In addition, Netball SA donated balls and will assist with netball coaching at the school in the future. BMi Research staff also spent time assisting the children with their lessons and working in the school&#x2019;s vegetable garden. Ubuhle Care and Development Centre was founded in 2008 by local women and men who work on a voluntary basis. Ubuhle offers social care, pre-school and an English primary school up to grade 7. The centre also provides after-school care, workshops and courses for adults as well as some aid to develop new income sources to 200 families living in the rural area. BMi Research has been supporting Ubuhle Care and Development Centre since its inception.